30 August 1997
MAF Staff Member Being Interviewed
Allegations have been made that a Ministry of Agriculture staff member has
been involved in the spread of rabbit calicivirus disease (RCD) in south
Canterbury. MAF is investigating the matter with assistance of the Police.
Investigations to date indicate that this person was not involved in the
importation of the virus into New Zealand.
The person concerned has been suspended.
No further comment will be made until the matter has been fully investigated.
Media inquiries to:
Grant Burney, Director Human Resources, MAF Quality
Management (025) 445 956
